  "prompt": "If ballots were cast by contributing money, who would win the 2016 election?",
  "response": "If ballots were cast based on campaign contributions in the 2016 U.S. presidential election, Donald Trump would likely have had an advantage over Hillary Clinton, despite her receiving more total contributions. Trump\u2019s campaign was known for its significant fundraising from individual donors, while Clinton had a strong backing from larger donations, including from PACs and organizations. \n\nHowever, since campaign contributions can come from a variety of sources and amounts, determining a clear winner based solely on financial contributions would require a detailed analysis of who contributed, how much, and the context of those contributions. Additionally, the influence of money in politics is complex, with many factors at play, beyond just the dollar amounts.",
